00:50:56.730 --> 00:50:58.430
Be my horses ready?

1053
00:50:58.430 --> 00:51:00.830
Thy asses are gone about 'em.

1054
00:51:02.930 --> 00:51:06.330
The reason why the seven starsare no more than seven

1055
00:51:06.330 --> 00:51:07.530
is a pretty reason.

1056
00:51:07.530 --> 00:51:08.600
Because they're not eight?

1057
00:51:08.600 --> 00:51:10.830
Yes, indeed.

1058
00:51:10.830 --> 00:51:13.000
Thou would make a good fool.

1059
00:51:13.000 --> 00:51:14.530
To take 't again perforce.

1060
00:51:14.530 --> 00:51:17.200
Monster ingratitude.

1061
00:51:17.200 --> 00:51:18.630
If thou wert my fool, nuncle,

1062
00:51:18.630 --> 00:51:22.670
I'ld have thee beaten for beingold before thy time.

1063
00:51:22.670 --> 00:51:24.530
How's that?

1064
00:51:28.530 --> 00:51:35.000
Thou shouldst not have been oldtill thou hadst been wise.

1065
00:51:37.100 --> 00:51:40.770
O, let me not be mad, not mad.

1066
00:51:40.770 --> 00:51:43.070
Sweet heaven, keep me in temper.

1067
00:51:43.070 --> 00:51:45.000
I would not be mad.

1068
00:51:45.000 --> 00:51:47.130
How now! Are my horses ready?

1069
00:51:47.130 --> 00:51:48.130
Ready, my lord.

1070
00:51:48.130 --> 00:51:49.470
Come, boy.

1071
00:51:54.700 --> 00:51:57.700
She that's a maid now and laughsat my departure

1072
00:51:57.700 --> 00:52:02.030
shall not be a maid long unlessthings be cut shorter.

